headline: Teradyne (TER): Assessing Valuation After Strong Multi-Period Share Price Gains
summary: Recent Performance Signals Growing Investor Interest Teradyne (TER) has been quietly rewarding patient investors, with the stock up about 7% over the past week and nearly 20% in the past month, significantly outpacing the broader semiconductor space. See our latest analysis for Teradyne. That short term strength is not happening in isolation, with Teradyne delivering a year to date share price return of about 57 percent and a three year total shareholder return of roughly 139 percent.
